methods.javadoc: Looks for situations where clients may lose the values added to this class. This most often happens when a client adds an anonymous, local listener to an object that is using a WeakSet to store its listeners. Our policy is to implement listeners at the class field level so that they will not be flagged by this method. @param t The object to check
methods.name: maybeWarnAboutAnonymousValue
methods.comment:
Looks for situations where clients may lose the values added to this class.  This
 most often happens when a client adds an anonymous, local listener to an object that is 
 using a WeakSet to store its listeners.  Our policy is to implement listeners at the 
 class field level so that they will not be flagged by this method.

fields.name: WARNING_MESSAGE
fields.constant_value:
"Added an anonymous class from a method or constructor.  Ghidra now has a policy of creating classes as top-level elements or creating inline classes where the field of the class is being declared.  This prevents accidental bugs whereby programmers add listeners to objects without maintaining a reference to that listener.
See SCR 8267 for an example."
